A good drill to do under pressure and build the lungs; go as far as you can go under water whilst maintaining technique and composure with paddles on. I’m not focusing much on my lower half with big fly kicks as I that’s not the objective. Repeat as many times as you want. 60m next week 🥴 Comment below what drills you want to see next👇🏼

I’ve learnt so much from 2019. I’ve had some incredible memories and also a few life changing moments. Heading into 2020 I aim to be more grateful for what I have and the people that surround me as they have been key to my growth as an athlete and as a person. ▪️▪️▪️
I’m so proud that my race clinics @apraceclinics have been a huge success with my blood brother @edwardbaxter98 leading the company to uncharted waters as we aim to go from 500 kids too 1000’s across the world next year! ▪️▪️▪️
Ofcourse I will continue to try and push the boundaries of my sport and I hope to inspire more people than ever with not only my performances but also my story. I’ve loved being part of @iswimleague and I hope it grows into something the sport truly deserves.
▪️▪️▪️
I 100% believe the energy you give in your actions, to people, by what you say and do is reciprocated so I want to continue pushing as much positivity as I can as I’ve learned the opposite makes life a lot harder when it doesn’t need to be; this mainly comes from the people you surround yourself with.
▪️▪️▪️
Big love to everyone who has supported me from my amazing sponsors to my incredible fans! I have a feeling this year will be big and I’ll always appreciate the people who have helped me achieve what I have! Have a great new year and see you in 2020 🚀🚀🚀 “Don’t let life just pass you by, enjoy the journey”
Drip drip drip 💧 📸 @minekasapoglu

Thankyou so much for all my birthday messages! (Still working through them) Had a blast on my clinic today, so good to see so much up and coming talent! It’s been a mad year but hopefully 25 will be even bigger 🚀🚀🚀
